	</BackstoryDef>

	<BackstoryDef ParentName="CFAR_Mercenary">
		<defName>CFAR_CivilMercenary2</defName>
		<title>captain</title>
		<titleShort>captain</titleShort>
		<description>Although [PAWN_nameDef] had no military background whatsoever, people ended up calling [PAWN_objective] captain—mostly because [PAWN_pronoun] flew around in a old freighter long enough for the name to stick. With [PAWN_possessive] roguish charm and smooth words, [PAWN_pronoun] made a tidy living bashing in the skulls of [PAWN_possessive] targets and locking down whatever contracts came [PAWN_possessive] way.</description>
		<forcedTraits>
			<Beauty>1</Beauty>
		</forcedTraits>
		<disallowedTraits>
			<Abrasive>0</Abrasive>
		</disallowedTraits>
		<skillGains>
			<Shooting>3</Shooting>
			<Social>6</Social>
		</skillGains>
		<spawnCategories>
			<li>CFAR_MercCivil</li>
		</spawnCategories>
	</BackstoryDef>

	<BackstoryDef ParentName="CFAR_Mercenary">
		<defName>CFAR_CivilMercenary3</defName>
		<title>ace pilot</title>
		<titleShort>ace</titleShort>
		<bodyTypeMale>Thin</bodyTypeMale>
		<bodyTypeFemale>Thin</bodyTypeFemale>
		<description>Deck of cards or a starfighter, [PAWN_nameDef] could handle either like an ace. [PAWN_pronoun] picked up the nickname at some backwater bar after winning three hands in a row with four-of-a-kind aces—apparently without cheating.</description>
